						               													<description>Plants&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#239;&amp;#187;&amp;#191;8 new Flora cards &amp;ndash; two for each habitat &amp;ndash; that are shuffled into the Animal cards and add new and interesting decisions to the gameplay.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Plants are guaranteed to photograph successfully but are not worth prestige at the end - you could use them to complete a Photography Award or even trigger the end of the game... but is it worth missing out on the prestige?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You can use these cards at any player count to add tactical depth.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Solo Mode&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You can now play the game solo using the &amp;quot;SnapBot&amp;quot; that uses a deck of cards to simulate another player to compete against for solo players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;SnapBot has a range of difficulty settings and recreates different player-interactions for an exciting and variable 1-player experience.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;5th Player&amp;#10;&amp;#10;By adding in the 8 plants, there are enough cards in the Animal card deck to sustain a 5-player game. The game plays much the same as the 2-4 player version so there are no new rules to learn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
